Program: Outlook
Title: 07/03/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00p6rx0
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 8 Mar 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, the Japanese doctor helping survivors of last year's devastating tsunami cope with their grief. We also hear the remarkable journey of Jin Xing - the former Chinese army colonel who had a sex change and is now one of the country's most celebrated modern dancers. And we hear how Brazil's blind ballet pupils learn arabesques and pirouettes. Show less